The paper deals with domain adaptation of visual detectors, which is a problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed approach involves using aligned-pair and/or pseudo-label losses to adapt an object detector to the target domain, which is a machine learning technique (cs.LG). The use of semantic segmentation annotations to condition the training of the transformation network involves the use of semantic information, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves the use of image processing techniques to generate cross-domain image pairs, which is a topic in multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper deals with object detection, which is a topic in robotics (cs.RO).
